tead? I also have worries about how SnakeYAML treats empty JSON content and how `URLDecoder.decode` handles certain characters. Additionally, I should think about whether I need `build.gradle` since it could fail if the module isn't included.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating build options**\\n\\nI’m figuring out that adding a native build argument doesn’t really change the compilation process. If the compile needs the module, I’d have to use `compileTestJava.options.compilerArgs += ['--add-modules','jdk.httpserver']`. But I think that `javac` can access `jdk.httpserver` classes directly from unnamed modules. \\n\\nSo, the default for unnamed modules includes `java.se` along with non-incubator modules that export packages. When using `com.sun.net.httpserver.HttpServer`, developers usually don’t add arguments. I also need to think about a user rule for managing test updates.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented coverage-focused test changes for `liquibase.hub.core.StandardHubService`.\n\nChanged files:\n- `tests/src/org.liquibase/liquibase-core/4.17.0/src/test/java/org_liquibase/liquibase_core/StandardHubServiceTest.java`\n  - Added a public dedicated test class for `StandardHubService`.\n  - Exercises `StandardHubService#getConnections(...)` through the public API.\n  - Uses a bounded local HTTP Hub stub to avoid external network calls.\n  - Verifies that Liquibase builds the Hub search query from `Connection` and nested `Project` fields, reaching:\n    - `Class#getDeclaredFields()`\n    - `Field#get(Object)`\n\n- `tests/src/org.liquibase/liquibase-core/4.17.0/build.gradle`\n  - Added native-image build module support for the JDK HTTP server used by the test:\n    - `--add-modules=jdk.httpserver`\n\nNo reachability metadata or native-image config files were edited. Tests were not run, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0a6cc3f14ab23b4b016a230575a4dc8193915cdb27fc20a81c\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "ope